article.description: James Woodard scored 19 points, Shaquille Harrison scored 11 and the go-ahead free throw in overtime and Tulsa rallied to beat Cincinnati 70-68 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Tulsa downs Cincinnati 70-68 in overtime behind Woodard
article.linkText: Tulsa downs Cincinnati 70-68 in overtime behind Woodard
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- James Woodard scored 19 points, Shaquille Harrison scored 11 and the go-ahead free throw in overtime and Tulsa rallied to beat Cincinnati 70-68 on Thursday night. Tied at 64, Cincinnati's Jacob Evans made a steal and was fouled, but split the pair of free throws and Tulsa pulled ahead 66-65 on Rashad Smith's jumper with a minute left. Harrison hit two free throws for a 68-65 lead, but Troy Caupain countered with a pair to pull Cincinnati within 68-67. Caupain fouled Pat Birt, who made both free throws for a 70-67 lead and Cincinnati's Shaq Thomas missed a 3 with one second left. Birt scored 13 and Smith had 12 for the Golden Hurricane (17-9, 9-5 American). Woodard heaved a shot three-quarters the length of the court at the buzzer to pull Tulsa within 32-27 at halftime, and Caupain tied it at 62 at the end of regulation with a layup. Gary Clark led Cincinnati (19-8, 9-5) with 18.
